Basic Problems
Array Sum: Write a program to find the sum of all elements in an array.
Maximum and Minimum: Find the maximum and minimum elements in an array.
Array Reversal: Reverse the elements of an array.
Element Search: Write a program to search for an element in an array (linear search).
Even and Odd Separation: Separate even and odd numbers in an array.
Intermediate Problems
Array Rotation: Rotate the array by k positions to the left.
Second Largest Element: Find the second largest element in an array.
Unique Elements: Remove duplicate elements from an array.
Merge Sorted Arrays: Merge two sorted arrays into one sorted array.
Subarray Sum: Find a subarray with a given sum.
Advanced Problems
Longest Consecutive Sequence: Find the longest consecutive sequence of elements in an unsorted array.
Array Pairs: Find all pairs in an array that sum up to a given number.
Product Array Puzzle: Construct an array where each element is the product of all elements in the original array except the current element.
Trapping Rain Water: Find the amount of water that can be trapped between the bars of an elevation map represented by an array.
Maximum Subarray: Implement Kadaneâ€™s algorithm to find the maximum sum subarray in an array.